---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NavBar from '../components/NavBar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use — Yard Metric"
  description="Terms of use for Yard Metric. Free calculators for estimation purposes. Results are not professional advice."
  canonical="https://yardmetric.com/terms/"
>
  <NavBar />

  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/" class="breadcrumb-link">Home</a>
          <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
          <span class="breadcrumb-current">Terms of Use</span>
        </nav>
        <h1 class="page-title">Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="page-lead">Last updated: June 2025</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="prose">

          <h2>Acceptance</h2>
          <p>
            By using Yard Metric you agree to these terms. If you do not agree,
            please do not use the site. We may update these terms at any time; continued use
            after changes constitutes acceptance.
          </p>

          <h2>Free to use</h2>
          <p>
            All calculators on this site are provided free of charge with no account or
            subscription required. We reserve the right to change, limit, or discontinue
            any feature at any time without notice.
          </p>

          <h2>Estimation only</h2>
          <p>
            Results produced by our calculators are estimates for planning and budgeting purposes
            only. They are not a substitute for professional advice from a licensed engineer,
            architect, contractor, or other qualified professional. Material quantities in the
            real world depend on site conditions, material variations, installation technique,
            and other factors no calculator can fully account for.
          </p>
          <p>
            Always verify quantities with your supplier before placing orders. We recommend
            adding a 5 to 10 percent overage to any estimate.
          </p>

          <h2>No warranty</h2>
          <p>
            This site and its calculators are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind,
            express or implied. We do not warrant that results are accurate, complete, or
            suitable for any particular purpose.
          </p>

          <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Yard Metric and its operators
            shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages
            arising from use of this site or reliance on calculator results. This includes, but
            is not limited to, costs from incorrect material orders, project delays, or
            construction errors.
          </p>

          <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
          <p>
            The design, code, and written content of this site are owned by Yard Metric. You may use the calculators freely for personal and commercial projects.
            You may not reproduce, scrape, or redistribute the site's content or code without
            written permission.
          </p>

          <h2>Third-party links</h2>
          <p>
            This site may link to external websites. We are not responsible for the content
            or practices of those sites.
          </p>

          <h2>Governing law</h2>
          <p>
            These terms are governed by applicable law without regard to conflict of law provisions.
          </p>

          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these terms? <a href="/contact/">Reach out to us</a> and we'll respond
            as quickly as we can.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
.container { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
.section { padding: 64px 0 80px; }
.hero { background: var(--color-canvas); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-hairline); padding: 40px 0 48px; }
.breadcrumb { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-mute); margin-bottom: 24px; }
.breadcrumb-link { color: var(--color-body); text-decoration: none; }
.breadcrumb-link:hover { color: var(--color-ink); }
.breadcrumb-sep { color: var(--color-hairline-strong); }
.breadcrumb-current { color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 500; }
.page-title { font-size: 40px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -1.8px; color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: 8px; }
.page-lead { font-size: 13px; color: var(--color-mute); font-family: var(--font-mono); }

.prose h2 { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.6px; color: var(--color-ink); margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
.prose h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
.prose p { font-size: 15px; color: var(--color-body); line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.prose a { color: var(--color-link); }
.prose a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

@media (max-width: 600px) { .container { padding: 0 16px; } .page-title { font-size: 32px; } }
</style>
